<br>
Brewing is probably the cheapest to take to 250 but you are doing 8 item (I think) combines to get beyond  180.  Then there isn't really a market for Brews.<br>
<br>
Smithing or Pottery is probably next.  I really can't comment on Smithing but Pottery you get a decent skill up rate but it's EXPENSIVE and ANNOYING.  You MUST have a Chanter to go beyond 188 (I have a Level 12 Chanter and for the most part that's enough).  The two items to go to mid 200 are Steins are Bands.  Bands require a LOT of vials of Mana from a Chanter while Steins take unstackable pieces of Enchanted Clay.  If you have a mule, the Steins are easier since you can buy C3 and just chain cast Enchant Clay (which is a Level 8 spell) and then dump them onto the person trying to skill up.<br>
<br>
Tailoring is just a total pain in the butt to raise past 158. <p>Baroness <A Href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6975" Style="text-decoration: none">Quistil Angelwatch</a><br>High Priest in the service to the Great Mother Tunare <br>
