<br>
A lot of people say that getting JC to 250 is expensive, but nine times out of ten you're talking to someone that's never done it. I got to 250 skill with about 3k. I felt kind of sheepish afterwards, because I hoarded 12k thinking I would need every last drop of it (again, listening to those &quot;experienced&quot; with the trade).<br>
<br>
I did it by boosting my INT to 217 and just grinding it out (this was pre-Luclin, so you'll have to forgive me). I did it in Qeynos... the vendors for gems and bars stand right next to each other. It *is*, however, tedious. I remember being 247 and doing combines for a few hours with no skill ups. Next thing you know, literally 10 minutes later I was 250 (I got two skill ups in a row, and one more not far after). Towards the tail end of JC'ing you can actually make a profit off of combines if you enchant the bars (by the way, you should already be there). Stick close to trivials and don't try to get too far ahead of yourself. Jewelcrafting is, by far, the easiest trade to master. You don't have to go digging god-knows-where for your components.<br>
<br>
